The most important change is that the dependency container is not instantiated anymore on each side effect. While the purpose of preventing the state in th
name: Mauro Bolis

author: bolismauro
message:
Add previousState in side effects

This commits completes the work of the previous commit. It adds the state before the updateState. In this way the side effect has all the information that are needed to properly take actions
name: Mauro Bolis

author: bolismauro
message:
Execute side effects after the update state

As discussed internally it seems that it is better to run the side effects after the updateState. By moving the side effects after the updateState we are able to have the updatedState when running custom logic

message:
Set View's props isUserInteractionEnabled to true by default

Views are very commonly used as containers for buttons and other controls. Having `isUserInteractionEnabled` set to false by default doesn't allow interaction with the contained components.

author: madbat

name: Matteo Battaglio

author: madbat
message:
Make Value conform to ExpressibleByIntegerLiteral and ExpressibleByFloatLiteral

This allows `Value` instances to be initialized by integer and floating
point literals, having the scalable part equal to the numeric literal,
and the fixed part equal to 0.
name: Matteo Battaglio
